=== TASK ===
# Export & Print-Ready Generation

## Overview
Implement a robust Export & Print-Ready Generation feature that enables teachers and parents to generate printable, paginated PDF exports (teacher-friendly format) and downloadable asset bundles (flashcards, answer keys). The system should support multiple paper sizes, printer-friendly stylesheets, and a queue-driven workflow for large exports with real-time progress updates, secure access controls, watermarking options for unpaid tiers, and secure asset packaging. Integrate with existing StudySpark project context (Study Spark – AI-Powered Personalized Study Builder for Kids) and wire into pages page_p008, page_p011, and page_p009.

Key outcomes:
- Generate high-quality, paginated PDFs from templates with flexible content (study sets, flashcards, answer keys, teacher notes).
- Produce downloadable asset bundles (zip files) containing flashcards, answer keys, and optional multimedia assets.
- Provide queueing, progress tracking, and user-friendly download links.
- Enforce access control, watermarking, and tier-based restrictions as needed.

---

## Components to Build

1) PDF Template Engine
- Purpose: Generate printable PDFs from data-driven templates with support for multiple paper sizes (A4, Letter, Legal) and printer-friendly CSS/print styles.
- Capabilities:
  - Template system supporting: study sheets, flashcards, answer keys, and teacher notes.
  - Server-side rendering using wkhtmltopdf, Puppeteer (Headless Chrome), or cloud PDF API.
  - Watermarking options for unpaid tiers.
  - Header/Footer, page numbers, and per-page content blocks.
  - Pagination control and content splitting for long study sets.
  - Support for embeds: images, scanned documents, and uploaded material references.
  - Accessible PDF considerations (tagged PDFs, readable text).
- Data flow:
  - Input data objects: studySet { title, topic, childAge, learningStyle, items[] }, assets[], teacherNotes, watermark, paperSize, margins, orientation.
  - Output: pdfBuffer or downloadable PDF URL, per-page metadata.

2) Asset Bundle Generator
- Purpose: Create downloadable bundles (zip) of assets such as flashcards, answer keys, and supplementary materials.
- Capabilities:
  - Generate flashcard sets in printable formats (PDF or image sheets) and as digital JSON/CSV bundles.
  - Generate answer keys aligned to questions; include metadata and versioning.
  - Bundle media assets (images, diagrams) with proper naming conventions.
  - Zip archive creation with deterministic naming (studyTitle_timestamp.zip).
  - Optional minified/optimized assets for performance.
- Data flow:
  - Input: bundleSpec { includeFlashcards, includeAnswers, includeMedia, format (pdf, images, json), quality } and content payload references.
  - Output: zipUrl or downloadable binary.

3) Export Queueing & Progress Service
- Purpose: Manage long-running export tasks with robust progress tracking and user notifications.
- Capabilities:
  - Job queue (RBQ/Redis, BullMQ, or AWS SQS) with retries and exponential backoff.
  - Progress events: queued, processing, rendering, completed, failed, partial success.
  - Per-user job correlation, permission checks, and rate limiting.
  - Real-time progress updates via WebSocket/SSE or polling endpoints.
  - Persist job state to database with timestamps, IDs, and result links.
- Data flow:
  - QueueJob: { userId, exportType, payloadRef, status, progress, resultLink, error }
  - Events: onProgress, onComplete, onError.

4) Access Control & Watermarking Module
- Purpose: Ensure secure access to exports; apply watermarking for unpaid tiers.
- Capabilities:
  - Tier-based access checks (free vs. paid users) for exports.
  - Watermark engine: apply watermark text/image overlays on PDFs (e.g., “StudySpark - Preview”).
  - Token-based secure temporary download links with expiry.
  - Audit logging for export access attempts.
- Data flow:
  - UserContext: { userId, tier, permissions }
  - Decisions: allowExport, applyWatermark(boolean)

5) Template System & Paper Sizes
- Purpose: Define reusable templates for study sheets, flashcards, and answer keys with support for multiple paper sizes.
- Capabilities:
  - Template definitions with placeholders: {title, topics, items, images, notes, pageBreaks}.
  - Style system for printer-friendly CSS/print rules.
  - Dynamic sizing rules per paperSize (A4, Letter, Legal) and orientation (portrait/landscape).
  - Theming hooks to interpolate color system from the project’s design system.
- Data flow:
  - TemplateCatalog: { id, name, type, paperSize, orientation, cssPrint, contentBlocks }

6) Frontend UI Components & Pages
- Pages:
  - page_p008: Initiate Export (PDF + bundles) with options (paper size, orientation, include sections, watermark flag, watermarked sample).
  - page_p011: Track Exports & Download (progress dashboard, status, and access to links).
  - page_p009: Manage Asset Bundles (flashcards, answer keys, media) with preview and download.
- Components:
  - ExportWizard: step-by-step UI for configuring exports.
  - ProgressPanel: shows progress, estimated time, and live status.
  - DownloadCard: downloadable asset or PDF with preview thumbnail.
  - JobList: list of active/completed export jobs with actions (retry, cancel).
  - WatermarkToggle: switch to apply watermark with preview badge.
  - PaperSizeSelector: responsive dropdown for A4/Letter/Legal with orientation.
  - BundlePreview: interactive preview of flashcards/answers in printable format.
- State & Data Handling:
  - Use React with TypeScript.
  - Implement robust null/undefined guards for all arrays (data ?? []) and Array.isArray checks.
  - Initialize useState([]) for arrays and useEffect-driven fetch with validation: const dataList = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
  - Ensure all list rendering uses safe guards before map/filter/reduce.

7) API Layer
- Backend APIs:
  - POST /api/exports/create to start an export job.
  - GET /api/exports/:jobId/status to fetch progress.
  - GET /api/exports/:jobId/download to obtain the final URL/file.
  - GET /api/bundles/:bundleId/download for asset bundles.
  - GET /api/templates to fetch available templates.
  - POST /api/security/watermark to generate watermark settings or preview.
- Database Tables:
  - exports: id, userId, exportType, status, progress, createdAt, updatedAt, resultUrl, watermarkEnabled, paperSize, orientation, includedSections.
  - bundles: id, exportId, bundleType, status, files, archiveUrl, createdAt.
  - templates: id, name, type, paperSize, orientation, cssPrint, createdAt, updatedAt.
  - users: id, tier, permissions (for watermarking and export rights).
  - audit_logs: id, userId, action, targetId, timestamp, details.
- Security:
  - JWT-based authentication; authorization guard for user permissions.
  - Rate limiting per user for export initiation.
  - Validate payload shapes with runtime checks; strict schemas.
- Validation:
  - Any array-based response must be checked: const items = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].

8) Integration Layer
- How components connect:
  - Frontend dispatches export requests to /api/exports/create with payload derived from ExportWizard state.
  - Backend validates user, selects templates, creates a queue job, and returns jobId.
  - Queueing service processes the job, renders PDFs via the PDF Template Engine, creates asset bundles if requested, applies watermarking, and updates job status.
  - Progress updates are pushed to the frontend via WebSocket/SSE or polled at /api/exports/:jobId/status.
  - On completion, a secure download link is stored (short-lived) and presented to the user in the Download panel.
  - Access control checks ensure only authorized users can download; unpaid users receive watermark and limited access.
- Data integrity:
  - All API responses are validated: const payload = Array.isArray(input?.payload) ? input.payload : [].
  - Use data ?? [] for any list results from external services like database or Supabase.
- Error handling:
  - Centralized error handler with user-friendly messages and telemetry.

---

## User Experience Flow

1) Initiation
- User navigates to Export page (page_p008) and begins a new export.
- User selects: paper size (A4/Letter/Legal), orientation (portrait/landscape), sections to include (study sheets, flashcards, answer keys, teacher notes).
- User can enable/disable watermarking (dependent on tier).
